    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "On further discussion in #8204 with @KaanKC, it is risky to access the duties of the next epoch, as it might change in the event of a deeper re-org. Two possible ways forward \r\n1) Close the issue and leave the current code as it is.\r\n2)  Remove the Next epoch Duties from the response payload and stop a node from requesting the next epoch's duties.\r\n\r\nThe major downside on going with 2) is that we have to modify our validator rpc schema, which isn't backwards compatible. So anyone running a beacon node with this change will not be compatible with older validator versions. \r\n@terencechain , thoughts ?",
